            <title>[CAMEL-3715] Sending to http endpoint may double encoding parameters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3715</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See nabble&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The workaround is to use either HTTP_URI or HTTP_QUERY as a header with the parameters. Then they are not double encoded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also the HTTP_URI should be placeholder resolved, so we can use &lt;tt&gt;port&lt;/tt&gt; or the likes to inject the port number dynamic.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
